## CONTEXT ‚Äî What changed

The `openclaw-control` repo now ships a `Dockerfile` that builds an ephemeral
Ansible control runner image (`openclaw-control:ci`).  This is a **third
execution context** for running Ansible against the VPS.

### Three execution contexts

| Context | Description | Who uses it |
|---|---|---|
| `LOCAL_SSH` | Ansible installed locally, SSH key at `~/.ssh/id_rsa` | Operator with Ansible |
| `LOCAL_DOCKER` | Docker runner image, no local Ansible needed | Operator with Docker |
| `GITHUB_ACTIONS` | workflow_dispatch ‚Üí ubuntu-latest runner ‚Üí Ansible | Link AI, operators via GitHub UI |

**Link's active context is still `GITHUB_ACTIONS`** ‚Äî unchanged.

### Docker runner details

- Image name: `openclaw-control:ci`
- Build: `docker build -t openclaw-control:ci .` (from repo root)
- Base: `python:3.11-slim` + `pip install ansible`
- Entrypoint: `ansible-playbook`
- Working dir inside container: `/work` (repo mounted at runtime)
- SSH keys: `$HOME/.ssh` mounted read-only at `/root/.ssh`

Full run command:
```bash
docker run --rm \
  -e ANSIBLE_HOST_KEY_CHECKING=False \
  -e ANSIBLE_SSH_ARGS="-F /dev/null" \
  -v "$PWD:/work" \
  -v "$HOME/.ssh:/root/.ssh:ro" \
  openclaw-control:ci \
  -i ansible/inventory ansible/site.yml --tags <tag>
```

### Bot execution model ‚Äî unchanged

All bots on srv1501082 run as **native systemd services**:
- `openclaw-agent.service` ‚Äî /opt/openclaw-agent/agent.py
- `openclaw-crypto.service` ‚Äî /home/jacks/openclaw-crypto/main.py (REAL GBP)
- `alpaca_orb_bite_bot.service` ‚Äî /home/jacks/alpaca_orb_bite_bot/main.py
- `linkedin-news.timer` + `linkedin-news.service` ‚Äî fires Sun 22:00 UTC

The Docker runner is on the **control side only** ‚Äî it does not run on the VPS.

